[start section id="20112"]

I discussed her situation with several of my colleagues in GI Oncology.  She has a difficult situation in that she cannot take oxaliplatin because of prior reaction in her MS.  I did discuss the fact that she had a-positive margin and felt she did need treatment.  I would therefore suggest treatment with 5-FU and leucovorin for six-months.  She could try Xeloda, but this might be more difficult for her than 5-FU.  Erbitux and Avastin have not been shown to be effective in the adjuvant setting so I would not use these, and I think also CPT-11 might be difficult for her.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: Yes, on file at Slinger Chiropractic Valley Nursing Home.

